commit_message:
Add update section to dashboard_databases.rst

The update section was present in the old
docbook version, but missing in the migrated
RST version.

This happened because the docbook update section
merged at the same time the RST file was being
created.

Change-Id: Ic341121c8248cbb3805659674a9494e3de15437a
Partial-Bug: #1440957

[{'created': '2015-03-24 10:31:43.000000000', 'message': 'Return None for missing trust_id in fixture

If the trust_id is unset it raises a KeyError. This is unusual from a
python perspective (if nothing else it should be AttributeError) and
different to all the other attributes of the fixture.

Return None if no trust_id is set on the fixture.

Change-Id: I15d33d77027a188fa47df18387c4610908f8e2d2
'}]
commit_message:
Return None for missing trust_id in fixture

If the trust_id is unset it raises a KeyError. This is unusual from a
python perspective (if nothing else it should be AttributeError) and
different to all the other attributes of the fixture.

Return None if no trust_id is set on the fixture.

Change-Id: I15d33d77027a188fa47df18387c4610908f8e2d2

commit_message:
Reduce dhcp agent calling 'reload_allocations'

this patch reduce dhcp agent calling driver method 'reload_allocations'
when operation 'port_update_end', 'port_create_end' and 'port_delete_end'
are in one network.

Change-Id: Ic79efd6583e2f306e067ba3b236e2b541e063871
Closes-Bug: #1437140

commit_message:
Fix fdb entries can't be removed

This patch fix that when a VM is migrated, the fdb entries in original
node can't be removed.

Change-Id: If48e7d26495756c57f2d4b738517b0201b485dc8
Closes-bug: #1438040

[{'created': '2015-03-24 08:39:28.000000000', 'message': 'Set volume_attachment to [] for the temporary volume creation

A new table volume_attachment has been added recently. During the
creation of the temporary volume, the attribute volume_attachment
is not empty if an attached volume is going to be migrated, so
this non-empty attribute leads to the failure of creation. This patch
removes this attribute before the temporary volume creation.

Change-Id: I7c2f69945ee8d72b2dba4e68a91b872207df5310
Closes-bug: #1433019
'}, {'created': '2015-03-24 08:44:22.000000000', 'message': 'Set volume_attachment to [] for the temporary volume creation

A new table volume_attachment has been added recently. During the
creation of the temporary volume in migration, the attribute
volume_attachment is not empty if an attached volume is going to be
migrated, because all the properties are simplily copied.
This non-empty attribute volume_attachment leads to the failure of
the volume creation. This patch removes this attribute before the
temporary volume creation.

Change-Id: I7c2f69945ee8d72b2dba4e68a91b872207df5310
Closes-bug: #1433019
'}, {'created': '2015-03-24 09:21:21.000000000', 'message': 'Set volume_attachment to [] for the temporary volume creation

A new table volume_attachment has been added recently. During the
creation of the temporary volume in migration, the attribute
volume_attachment is not empty if an attached volume is going to be
migrated, because all the properties are simplily copied.
This non-empty attribute volume_attachment leads to the failure of
the volume creation. This patch removes this attribute before the
temporary volume creation.

Besides, detach the volume should consider multi-attach as well by
adding the attachment id parameter.

commit_message:
Set volume_attachment to [] for the temporary volume creation

A new table volume_attachment has been added recently. During the
creation of the temporary volume in migration, the attribute
volume_attachment is not empty if an attached volume is going to be
migrated, because all the properties are simply copied.
This non-empty attribute volume_attachment leads to the failure of
the volume creation. This patch removes this attribute before the
temporary volume creation.

Besides, detach the volume should consider multi-attach as well by
adding the attachment id parameter.

Change-Id: I7c2f69945ee8d72b2dba4e68a91b872207df5310
Closes-bug: #1433019

Adding documentation for guide pages in horizon

Adding documentation for the cluster and job guides
in horizon.

commit_message:
Implement caching for constraint validation

The specification describes changes in validation of
property constaints. It allows to reduce number of API
requests to other components.

blueprint constraint-validation-cache

Change-Id: Ifc51ecf7f52900dd808c5d64ed600acd951fedb5

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-04-02 13:19:33.000000000', 'message': "FIX Vm stuck when deploying with pxe_ssh + local boot

When deploying a machine with the DIB ramdisk, pxe_ssh driver and
local boot the VM will keep rebooting forever after the deployment is
completed. This happens because Ironic will change the boot device from
PXE to DISK as part of the deployment but the change will only take effect
after the VM is powered off and on again (that's a virsh problem). This
patch is fixing this problem by making Ironic reboot the machine after

commit_message:
Fix VM stuck when deploying with pxe_ssh + local boot

When deploying a machine with the DIB ramdisk, pxe_ssh driver and
local boot the VM will keep rebooting forever after the deployment is
completed. This happens because Ironic will change the boot device from
PXE to DISK as part of the deployment but the change will only take effect
after the VM is powered off and on again (that's a virsh problem). This
patch is fixing this problem by making Ironic reboot the machine after
the deployment is completed (reboot in Ironic means power it off and
on again).

Closes-Bug: #1439664
Change-Id: I4aa859b00a8bba186e920e09734ec2e4c45dec3e

commit_message:
Allow providing a node stringify function to tree pformat

Allow providing a node to string function that will be activated
when the root node pformat routine needs to format a node into
a string (for viewing purposes); this allows for subclasses or
other users of nodes to provide there own function that they can
specialize as they see fit (without duplicating the pformat
routine itself).

To start use it to print out the node link target in the fake
in-memory filesystem when a link is encountered.

Change-Id: I33b8f1ec8d30d72ae35971e35f5edd84a9145db7

[{'created': '2015-04-07 18:40:31.000000000', 'message': 'Update redis system.py paths for current RHEL/CentOS/Fedora

Some of the paths currently defined in the "redhat" stanza
of the redis guestagent datastore code don't match the
redis packages currently available for Fedora/CentOS/RHEL.

Change-Id: I09fb5e426db57ed76ff23ee6c230229039a3897d
Closes-Bug: #1440785
'}]
commit_message:
Update redis system.py paths for current RHEL/CentOS/Fedora

Some of the paths currently defined in the "redhat" stanza
of the redis guestagent datastore code don't match the
redis packages currently available for Fedora/CentOS/RHEL.

Change-Id: I09fb5e426db57ed76ff23ee6c230229039a3897d
Closes-Bug: #1440785

commit_message:
Fixes config templates for mysql & percona

Calculations for certain config parameters was resulting in zero
if a value < 512 was used as ram for flavors to boot guest instance.

Replaced '//' by '/' and the result is again casted to integer value
as needed by mysql configurations.

// implies divide two numbers and return
the truncated integer result.

whereas

/ implies divide two numbers and  return value
will be a floating point number.

Updated default instance configuration response json.

Change-Id: Icfc84a4cb380264670aa4e31f372eb39a6e87c7c
Closes-Bug: #1440358

commit_message:
Fix Enum field, which allows unrestricted values

For some reason, the Enum field allows valid_values to be None, which disables
all the is-this-a-valid-value checking, thus defeating the entire purpose of
the type. This patch removes that possibility so that we don't let anything
creep into the RPC-affecting API that would be unrestricted.

The change that introduced this was I7848f8b934c169a76b1cfd875f7905273f9f914b

Closes-Bug: #1441243
Change-Id: Ia33994402cca5b4569d72860ab5da675134f5a95

commit_message:
Mock resource to emulate various behaviors.

Functional tests require resources with finer control over their
behavior. For example, tests require a resource to emulate failure to
test rollback, or emulate update-in-place to test certain scenarios of
stack update.

Functional tests and the mocked resource code for review:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/170682/

Change-Id: I4c1ca814b10a7b92854cae86116f840881911237

commit_message:
Fix bad quoting in quickstart guide

Before, the " and ' in the message was rendering into smart quotes,
making copy+paste impossible. This fix places the commands inside the
note into a blockquote, preventing sphinx from breaking copy+paste.

Change-Id: I7291f7cbdb9c7fa16d23376792012a7a70c7c16b

commit_message:
Set hash seed to 0 in gendocs environment

This was done in the venv environment to fix docs builds in the gate,
but they still fail randonly locally when using the tox environment to
build them. This change ensures the gendocs environment works for
generating documentation locally.

Change-Id: I41e4af9edaaa76b837a6c92a296b5738c85b632b

commit_message:
Enhance TESTING.rst

Add detail about api testing and provide better visual separation
between the different types of testing.

The current testing guidelines are mainly about running tests, and
this change does little to fix that.  The intention is to add detail
about writing tests in subsequent changes.

Change-Id: I39d0439c91e5c6edb1d48d4da310443c99fb6d9e

commit_message:
tests: add a ServersTestBase class

Split general purpose methods out of the ServersTest class to a
new ServersTestBase class, to be used with a future server tests
classes.

Change-Id: Iacb0b6da9bc07b0ed3d43e630db3fac3f6e751ee

commit_message:
tests: enhance functional tests primitives

Adding a method to create a new flavor with or without an extra_spec,
and a method to create a full server configuration, using a flavor_id.
This will allow the functional tests to build custom test servers.

Also splitting the setup_services method in _IntegratedTestBase in to
separate methods, for the functional tests to override it and
control the initialization of each service.

Change-Id: Ic5ef388f5daae7394d20bda5ed1db6f718564dbc

In the scenario tests create_server helper method the returned network
from get_tenant_network() was not being used it was returned and the
method to add it to the kwargs dict was called, but the resulting
updated dict was never used. This patch corrects the oversight by
updating the kwargs dict to ensure we actually pass the right network
into the create server call.

Change-Id: I1976ed6eb2edfa77971bd908fe47514c1a801b98
'}]
commit_message:
Use network from get_tenant_network in scenario

In the scenario tests create_server helper method the returned network
from get_tenant_network() was not being used it was returned and the
method to add it to the kwargs dict was called, but the resulting
updated dict was never used. This patch corrects the oversight by
updating the kwargs dict to ensure we actually pass the right network
into the create server call.

Change-Id: I1976ed6eb2edfa77971bd908fe47514c1a801b98

Use the catalog to discover available services instead of get_service

This script should not require admin creds and that was the reason it did.

Sync with oslo.incubator

Add oslo.policy and oslo.concurrency to oslo config generator extra
libraries to retrieve config options
Update oslo_incubator service module
Update oslo_incubator versionutils with new list_opts discovery

commit_message:
Shorten time for unittest test_download_with_retries

The unit test:
ironic.tests.test_glance_service.TestGlanceImageService.test_download_with_retries

was taking over 1 second to complete.  After mocking time.sleep the unit
test no longer shows up in the slowest test list.

Change-Id: I060f1e9632efff5a57e43aac273669211fb44f0a

commit_message:
remove unneeded teardown related code

The DatabaseFixture ensures we have a blank database at the beginning
of a test, previously there was a teardown method here, which was
deleted. However there remains a bunch of state tracking which was
related to that teardown. Cleanup up all the extra variable references
to avoid future confusion with this test.

Change-Id: I5527413dfcc6b9e0691bfc229247e7707b75cb45

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-04-07 15:37:35.000000000', 'message': "VPNaaS: Reorganize test tree

Similar to what is happening in Neutron, this commit renames and moves unit
test files so that they match the directory structure of the code tree.
Since the VPN repo's test files have imports from Neutron, there are import
changes as well, to the imports to match the Neutron test file organization.

A check script is added to monitor the test file naming and locations (to
ensure consistency).

Also, bash scripts are changed to use '#!/usr/bin/env bash' and the

commit_message:
VPNaaS: Reorganize test tree

Similar to what is happening in Neutron, this commit renames and moves unit
test files so that they match the directory structure of the code tree.
Since the VPN repo's test files have imports from Neutron, there are import
changes as well, to the imports to match the Neutron test file organization.

A check script is added to monitor the test file naming and locations (to
ensure consistency).

Change-Id: I875285230127ed660137d271f7e98d82eb57ffab
Partial-Bug: #1440834

commit_message:
Make devstack-gate stable release tests non-voting

Split out devstack-gate tests we're running from tempest, which
wants to keep them voting, and make the devstack-gate tests
non-voting for the stable release checks.

Change-Id: I0d82180fcea02cdb91b863cae15eedf19d183514

[{'created': '2015-03-05 20:59:39.000000000', 'message': "Add checksum rules to allow tempest network tests

This fix addresses checksum errors when the tempest container tries to
check network connectivity between itself and a cirross image on an AIO.
The checksums are not filled because there is no physical interface
involved, and therefore the container and the VM must have it's traffic
checksummed.

Partial-Bug: #1425255
Change-Id: Ib9f5193c4c7707476641711ebf7250ec5cabf8e6
"}]
commit_message:
Add checksum rules to allow tempest network tests

This fix addresses checksum errors when the tempest container tries to
check network connectivity between itself and a cirross image on an AIO.
The checksums are not filled because there is no physical interface
involved, and therefore the container and the VM must have it's traffic
checksummed.

Partial-Bug: #1425255
Change-Id: Ib9f5193c4c7707476641711ebf7250ec5cabf8e6

correctly rendered.

Fix Rspec 3.x new is_expected.[to|to_not] keywords

Some 'should' keyword have been forgotten during the rspec2.x to rspec3.x
updates. This patch fixes that!

commit_message:
Remove check for bash usage

Arbitrarily restricting ourselves from using bash because developers on
platforms like netbsd don't want to install bash from ports doesn't
make sense.  Any non-trivial shell script is likely to use features
like arrays or string manipulation that are poorly supported (if at
all) by sh, and the continued bumping of the number of expected bash
scripts is an indication that the check is not serving its purpose
anyway.

Along with removing the check, all shebang references to /bin/bash
have been replaced with /usr/bin/env bash in an attempt to be more
compatible across different hosts.

Change-Id: Ief72dc380cc88af38959c330897e2c127e33c332
Closes-Bug: #1440824

This seems like something that test-matrix.py should be doing not devstack-vm-gate.sh.'}, {'account_id': 10980, 'date': '2015-03-23 20:45:48.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

I started looking there, but it didn't seem to fit well, nor does it catch all the methods of setting services.  Can you hum a few more bars?

This file is what I'm trying to cleanup: https://github.com/openstack/neutron-lbaas/blob/master/neutron_lbaas/tests/contrib/gate_hook.sh

And I did something even more horrible for my third-party CI, that I'd also like to cleanup."}, {'account_id': 4146, 'date': '2015-04-06 23:00:36.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

My suggestion would be to simply specify the services you need in a different features.yaml file. One reason we describe the services in a file that can be overridden like that is so that you can easily override the defaults shipped by d-g.'}, {'account_id': 4146, 'date': '2015-04-06 23:03:12.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Another alternative is to update the service list using the existing ENABLE_SERVICES appending and hvae devstack sort it out.'}, {'account_id': 10980, 'date': '2015-04-07 00:52:58.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Thanks. I think ENABLED_SERVICES= gets stomped by d-g, and you have to either use features.yml or OVERRIDE_ENABLE_SERVICES.

My issue with either of those mechanisms is that you have to specify a complete list.  There is no way to say, "give me the default list, but with these changes", nor is there a hook to edit the generated list before devstack runs.

I was hoping to use the *default* features.yaml services, and just tweak it, because there is value in the default services list being maintained by infra.'}, {'account_id': 4146, 'date': '2015-04-07 15:32:43.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

As noted on irc, ENABLED_SERVICES should not be stomped by d-g and devstack should support -Service1,Service2 to disable Service1 and enable Service2. So a string like this can be placed in ENABLED_SERVICES to modify the results of processing features.yaml.

If that all works as expected (and if it doesn't its probably a bug that should be fixed), this change should be abandoned."}, {'account_id': 10980, 'date': '2015-04-07 17:24:42.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

I agree.  I already have a test up here: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/171049/

But the gate breakage last night got in the way of me finishing the test.  Expect a confirm/abandon today.  Thanks.'}, {'account_id': 10980, 'date': '2015-04-07 22:42:26.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

As pointed out, you can pass negations to devstack via ENABLED_SERVICES.'}]

commit_message:
Fix multipath device discovery when UFN is enabled.

This currently returns an invalid path of `/dev/mapper/${WWID}`
when UFN is enabled leading to failures later on when we attempt to
use the device.

The output of `multipath -l ${path}` or `multipath -l ${wwid}`
should always list the correct device identifier to use with this
path as the first word on the first line.

The same change has been suggested for both Cinder [1] and Nova [2]
as they are also susceptible to this issue.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/170157/
[2] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/169873/

Change-Id: I4a2d0e6ba4522ebfa0c50be49f7039f6e4617ae8
Closes-Bug: 1401799

commit_message:
Migrate to oslo.policy lib instead of copy-pasted oslo-incubator

The first official oslo.policy was released and so we're ready to
migrate from the copy-pasted oslo-incubator code to the separated
lib.

Change-Id: I8e404d2b622876389d9b1019ae50f1e1a8cecdf1

commit_message:
Update vanilla plugin doc

This patch updates vanilla plugin docs. Hive service was added in Kilo.
Also remove outdated links to images, because 2.4.1 version is
deprecated now, and vanilla image should contain hive component.

Change-Id: Ibd105e979afe1ffe6c221ffa7e4f0d2506aa028d

commit_message:
Add env_file support for docker-compose hook

Added support for `env_file` which can be single file or a list
of files. Use special input 'env_files' for the env_files. These
files will be created by the hook relative to the compose project
directory.

if 'env_file' entries in 'docker-compose.yml' do not exist in the
`input_values` supplied, docker-compose will throw an error as it
can't find these files.

Change-Id: I0dbe80e8c8c56cc680f8ee86b4f34cf3d27533c4

commit_message:
Removed unused injections in launch-instance-config step

We are injecting a few things in LaunchInstanceConfigurationCtrl that we
are not using. This patch removes those injections.

Change-Id: I44dbc5ca0e30569326809382ebdefeef6047d6d9
Closes-bug: #1440839

commit_message:
Adding Rally to OpenStack

Rally is a tool that simplifies testing, performance analysis and
benchmarking of all OpenStack clouds.

Our mission is to provide OpenStack ecosystem with framework and tool
that answer the question "How well OpenStack performs" and help developers
to improve OpenStack:

  - Rally tasks as a common language between QA/Dev/Ops and community
  - Simplify reproduction of performance/scale issues and races
  - Rally gate jobs that allows developers to
    work on performance/scale issues and races together in gates
  - Performance regression testing in gates and on scale
  - Automation of cloud performance validation

The Rally contributor community being made up of more then 135
developers from more then 36 companies.

Boris Pavlovic was selected as the PTL by Rally contributors according
to standard OpenStack community practices.

Our meetings are weekly, on IRC, and our road map is transparent and
managed via specs, feature requests, launchpad, Google drive and
other OpenStack community practices.

Change-Id: I53d42e5bff9217160703768e3d9643e4d1f9ecfa

commit_message:
Remove integrated-gate template from heat

Now that heat has its own job that runs just the heat tests in tempest,
stop running the tempest-full jobs from integrated-gate on heat.

This will remove:
* tempest-dsvm-full
* tempest-dsvm-postgres-full
* tempest-dsvm-neutron-full

Change-Id: Ib1c80f979bca9835d4e2d1e51a15db5ffb0128ca

commit_message:
Make PEM file conform with SSH Driver

SSH Driver uses a single PEM file to handle
SNI so an explicit file name is not necessary
any longer.

Change-Id: I1c117f68cb46a7cb72165143f62ed94669566727

commit_message:
Adds the openstack/tripleo-common to TripleO...

Propose adding openstack/tripleo-common to the TripleO
program. tripleo-common will be a python library
which will contain code common for Tuskar UI and TripleO CLI.

Change-Id: I5ae63c2ca3a5253897848b1e52a4475ebbd6b178

With MySQL 5.6 setup to use UTF-8 for everything, the 033 migration
will fail. This is because a VARCHAR(256) cannot be indexed in UTF-8
databases. In versions of MySQL before 5.6, this produced a warning and
a truncated, less-useful index. In 5.6 it was changed to an error.

We will reduce these columns further to 64 bytes in the model in a
subsequent fix. For now, we will just create the table with 64 character
columns on new systems, which will allow this migration to work properly
on mysql-5.6. There is no danger of overflow, as 64 chars is what Keystone
uses for them anyway.

commit_message:
Patch 033 migration to work w/ MySQL 5.6

With MySQL 5.6 setup to use UTF-8 for everything, the 033 migration
will fail. This is because a VARCHAR(256) cannot be indexed in UTF-8
databases. In versions of MySQL before 5.6, this produced a warning and
a truncated, less-useful index. In 5.6 it was changed to an error.

We will reduce these columns further to 64 bytes in the model in a
subsequent fix. For now, we will just create the table with 64 character
columns on new systems, which will allow this migration to work properly
on mysql-5.6. There is no danger of overflow, as 64 chars is what Keystone
uses for them anyway.

Closes-Bug: #1316646
(cherry picked from commit db0a7fe91d3eddc6d337028332fbd496bb000df2)

Change-Id: I27b9c61828301ba8c392b3d316f656641af753bc

commit_message:
Add puppet-diskimage_builder module

There are several things we need on any node that uses
diskimage-builder. Encapsulate them into a module so that when we need
diskimage-builder installed on multiple nodes, we don't have to cut and
paste a ton of stuff.

Depends-On: If55370ff2597cd0ffa97e6409ce411db4f08ad6f
Change-Id: Ic3684a9980181daae78e3fd5750ceee4aa807411

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-04-01 14:36:12.000000000', 'message': 'Add "release:has-stable-branches" tag

This tag lets us differentiate between projects that happen
to have stable branch cut out of their last release in the
development cycle (like Oslo libraries or Python client libs)
and projects that consciously make a release at the very end
of the 6-month development cycle to match with the "managed"
coordinated release (like Swift or Manila).

Those are different bits of information to convey to our users
(will they have a release to match with the coordinated 6-month
release, vs. will they have a stable branch to draw
backward-compatible safe updates from).

To make it easier to judge what that means, this change directly
applies the new tag to the existing set of projects.

I also clarified the meaning of the "release:at-6mo-cycle-end" tag
and removed it from projects that don't make a coordinated release.

Change-Id: Icb3b5a348e0a45437d6ac6a044ed098c6380ee97
'}]
commit_message:
Add "release:has-stable-branches" tag

This tag lets us differentiate between projects that happen
to have stable branch cut out of their last release in the
development cycle (like Oslo libraries or Python client libs)
and projects that consciously make a release at the very end
of the 6-month development cycle to match with the "managed"
coordinated release (like Swift or Manila).

Those are different bits of information to convey to our users
(will they have a release to match with the coordinated 6-month
release, vs. will they have a stable branch to draw
backward-compatible safe updates from).

To make it easier to judge what that means, this change directly
applies the new tag to the existing set of projects.

I also clarified the meaning of the "release:at-6mo-cycle-end" tag
and removed it from projects that don't make a coordinated release.

Change-Id: Icb3b5a348e0a45437d6ac6a044ed098c6380ee97

commit_message:
Add a two-organization rule to the diverse-affiliation tag

Thierry suggested the addition of a two-organization rule during the
review of the team:diverse-affiliation tag.  This patch adds that rule
and notes that it does not trigger any changes to the application of
the tag at this point.  However, it comes close for Trove.

This patch also includes a wording change from "company" to
"organization" in the tag definition, which was suggested by Anne
during the original review.

Change-Id: I132aa31a2c33580685619c41ec2d7d7a84d858c5

commit_message:
Apply the team:diverse-affiliation tag

This patch applies the team:diverse-affiliation tag to the teams that
meet the criteria.

So far we've only defined tags as applying to projects (git repos).
However, this tag is defined as applying to the sum of the team's
work.  So, I propose applying this tag at the team level.  Any tags
applied at the team level can be inherited by every git repo the
team manages.  This reduces a *lot* of unnecessary duplication of this
tag in the yaml file.

The following teams receive the tag:

  <Team> (top commit % | top review % | top core review % | (top core reviewer %)
  Nova               (19.61% | 19.85% | 25.50% | 31.25%)
  Swift              (27.31% | 26.42% | 37.15% | 36.36%)
  Glance             (23.37% | 29.19% | 39.84% | 33.33%)
  Keystone           (42.62% | 29.91% | 46.61% | 37.50%)
  Horizon            (27.97% | 16.94% | 22.53% | 30.77%)
  Neutron            (26.50% | 19.63% | 24.44% | 16.67%)
  Cinder             (11.73% | 11.33% | 16.68% | 20.00%)
  Heat               (33.10% | 33.98% | 38.75% | 27.78%)
  Trove              (35.16% | 38.89% | 47.22% | 42.86%)
  Ironic             (26.79% | 28.23% | 31.09% | 33.33%)
  Oslo               (31.18% | 28.08% | 34.42% | 23.08%)
  Infrastructure     (39.10% | 49.58% | 48.20% | 40.91%)
  Documentation      (19.68% | 26.75% | 35.92% | 19.05%)
  Quality Assurance  (26.90% | 26.17% | 32.39% | 33.33%)
  Magnum             (32.10% | 35.80% | 36.81% | 28.57%)

The following teams do not receive the tag:

  Barbican           (51.09% | 48.49% | 52.67% | 55.56%)
  Ceilometer         (52.33% | 31.96% | 63.04% | 50.00%)
  Designate          (56.50% | 64.63% | 65.49% | 60.00%)
  Manila             (47.77% | 30.60% | 44.93% | 50.00%)
  Murano             (85.14% | 91.99% | 99.33% | 87.50%)
  OpenStackClient    (34.50% | 36.22% | 56.21% | 33.33%)
  Sahara             (52.52% | 58.97% | 60.35% | 57.14%)
  TripleO            (54.89% | 56.66% | 62.67% | 60.87%)
  Zaqar              (48.89% | 67.11% | 77.99% | 66.67%)

Change-Id: I7a71ebb508d3f8d2fd8d9e33f920e2de70ebb7a4

commit_message:
Improved policy setting in the 'v3 filter' tests

The test case class IdentityTestListLimitCase (test_v3_filters.py)
always sets multiple policies for the each test defined in that class.
However, only one policy is really needed for each test case.
That appears to lead to unreliable policy checking.
It would be better to set only one policy required for the particular
test case (policy with the type of entity used in the test case).

Change-Id: I7892950b43c56ecce03677d8d592e71359bedf27
Closes-Bug: #1271273

subject: Add datasource synchronizer
revisions:
[{'created': '2015-04-07 20:29:44.000000000', 'message': 'Add datasource synchronizer

The datasource synchronizer reads from the configuration database on a
periodic basis and checks whether the active datasources match the
configuration in the database.  If the two do to match, the
synchronizer changes the active datasources to match the database.

By default, datasource synchronization is off.  To enable it, add a
line like this
   datasource_sync_period = 60
to the congress.conf configuration file.

This change includes a change to the datasource status API semantics.
The previous version of the status handler first checks that the
datasource exists in the database; if the datasource does not the
handler responds to the client with and error because the running
state in the server always matches the database content because there
can be just one Congress server modifying the database.  With the
basic high-availability solution, one congress server replica can
modify the database without a second replica knowing, so the running
state of the datasources can become out of sync with the database.

The new version of the datasource status API call returns the status
of the datasource if the datasource is running in the server, even if
the database does not contain the datasource.

This change also makes the list-datasources API call update the
running datasources to match the database after fetching the
datasource configuration from the database.

This also adds a tempest test to verify that datasource
synchronization works.

Implements blueprint: basic-high-availability
Change-Id: I732c965c616f0f11d4d30f7f90b0cce980f9342d

commit_message:
Add datasource synchronizer

The datasource synchronizer reads from the configuration database on a
periodic basis and checks whether the active datasources match the
configuration in the database.  If the two do to match, the
synchronizer changes the active datasources to match the database.

By default, datasource synchronization is off.  To enable it, add a
line like this
   datasource_sync_period = 60
to the congress.conf configuration file.

This change includes a change to the datasource status API semantics.
The previous version of the status handler first checks that the
datasource exists in the database; if the datasource does not the
handler responds to the client with and error because the running
state in the server always matches the database content because there
can be just one Congress server modifying the database.  With the
basic high-availability solution, one congress server replica can
modify the database without a second replica knowing, so the running
state of the datasources can become out of sync with the database.

The new version of the datasource status API call returns the status
of the datasource if the datasource is running in the server, even if
the database does not contain the datasource.

This change also makes the list-datasources API call update the
running datasources to match the database after fetching the
datasource configuration from the database.

This also adds a tempest test to verify that datasource
synchronization works.

Implements blueprint: basic-high-availability
Change-Id: I732c965c616f0f11d4d30f7f90b0cce980f9342d

fixes

Change-Id: I9d86d0c05d98bd3dcdfcbe92623ab8d6e0b78f11

Address comments

Change-Id: Ibacf514c64f6b632a858c1e94ae3b619b0509d0c

commit_message:
Adding the security team.

The VMT and the OSSG have merged to form a single security team.

We are seeking to have this team recognised as a horizontal project
within OpenStack, similar in many ways to the current documentation
team.

Advisories, Documentation, Security Notes, Threat Analysis etc
are all measured through their respective respositories.

Change-Id: I9d0db560952380d3283ca710608ed0fdd3af64da

commit_message:
Update Cloudera plugin docs

Changes:
 * update validation rules in docs;
 * Separate supported services for different plugin versions
 * add example how to build image for cdh.

Change-Id: Ifa2768b1a21f9d2a8f561925c93b6344e2915d8b

commit_message:
Check status of bootloader installation for DIB ramdisk

This commit adds a new vendor passthru
'pass_bootloader_install_info' for DIB ramdisk to
notify the status of boot loader installation. The
same change is made for both pxe_* drivers and iscsi_ilo
driver.

Closes-Bug: 1422723
Depends-on: I9c1d8643be7cb9e273d65ddd791715a5c271fd93
Change-Id: I9944b6835e42cc9b282b7a7b90191a18d00f2e38

commit_message:
Update nova-powervm for new mapping logic

The pypowervm library recently changed how it accepts vSCSI mappings.
The logic now works based off the core elements rather than mappings.
This change provides the necessary updates within nova-powervm to
support the new library method.

This also accomodates a change in pypowervm where the upload of the vOpt
now returns the vOpt wrapper.

Change-Id: Idffd56781b850fa239d7cfa87aa3fbaeceee3e4b

commit_message:
Follow the hosting chain to find the host server

Since a hosting chain may exist among several node templates (e.g.
a web application hosted on an application server, the application
server hosted on a web server, the web server hosted on a compute
node) update the code to follow the chain and return the actual
compute node host. The unit test for this patch will be covered by
bug #1435545.

Change-Id: I01bab61bc45b4031cd106295d216982332361b6b
Closes-Bug: #1439444
Partial-Bug: #1435545

commit_message:
Create a sync_db boolean for Heat.

Other components offer the option to decide whether or not to run the
db sync command. Heat was missing this feature. This commit add this
feature for Heat.

Change-Id: I06b669123fe08e02c66ee34dab78a943ff5de90c

commit_message:
Add workbook and workflow validate commands

Add workbook-validate and workflow-validate commands to validate
workbook and workflow definition respectively. The commands print
the error if validation fails else returns command prompt.

Change-Id: I25b220a2a9abd720f24ee6b23ce37ee977845793
Implements: blueprint api-validate-dsl

commit_message:
Fixed sort key to not sort by an un-indexed field by default

* Added indices on domain, record and recordset tables for created_at
* Removed redundent extra sort param in _find()

Partially-Fixes: #1413472

commit_message:
First Tempest tests for recordsets

* Added decorators for parameterized tests
* Added models/clients for recordsets
* Move v2 specific clients into DesignateV2Test base class
* Added data generation for A, AAAA, CNAME, and MX recordsets
* Added test cases that do CRUD on A, AAAA, CNAME, and MX recordsets

Change-Id: I7755167b707ca66f8f2a3362579e3e976b4aa315

commit_message:
Move elasticsearch dependency to test-requirements.txt

The glance catalog index service is optional so move the elasticsearch
dependency to test-requirements.txt.  This is important since
elasticsearch requires openjdk and some might not want to be forced into
installing that just to use glance.

Closes-Bug: #1441239

Change-Id: I6cd9642ecd363e660fea93eb18c3d9add5ead8b1

While we set the configuration option in DEFAULT section, we get the

commit_message:
Stop using deprecated DEFAULT group for lock_path

While we set the configuration option in DEFAULT section, we get the
following deprecation message in our logs:

WARNING oslo_config.cfg [-] Option "lock_path" from group "DEFAULT" is
deprecated. Use option "lock_path" from group "oslo_concurrency".

Switch to the new configuration option location.

Change-Id: I89783cc975a4a845ee57920d83236d6eb698af9c

commit_message:
Fix for notifications for v2 role grant/delete

Notifications were not being sent when role grants were added or
deleted using the v2 API.

SecurityImpact

Change-Id: I577d4435d551181298b23e713ed84f76d9f1ba3e
Closes-Bug: #1435396

commit_message:
Add index to the revocation_event.revoked_at.

`revocation_event` model class missed index at revoked_at column, whereas a
migration keystone/contrib/revoke/migrate_repo/versions/001_revoke_table.py:35
provides the index. The migration looks correct, but the model doesn't
appropriate to the migration.

Closes-Bug: #1397899
Change-Id: I5205f9a0e951d43badd2b11fd5b20a5d59c07ee8

Fix help string for glance auth_strategy option

Help for Glance auth_strategy config option is incorrect, this change
fixes it.

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-04-03 00:33:58.000000000', 'message': 'Fix dynamic arp populate error for dvr routers

Recent refactor to the L3 Agent have introduced
this problem. When we create a VM after we
attach an interface to a router or when we add
an interface with an existing VM to a router, in
both cases the arp entries for the dvr serviced
ports are not getting populated in the Router
Namespace.

This patch will fix that issue.

Change-Id: I4a82e2435d176f3d9336d7f0dab9726c063840b9
Closes-Bug: #1438969

commit_message:
Fix dynamic arp populate error for dvr routers

Recent refactor to the L3 Agent have introduced
this problem. When we create a VM after we
attach an interface to a router or when we add
an interface with an existing VM to a router, in
both cases the arp entries for the dvr serviced
ports are not getting populated in the Router
Namespace.

Closes-Bug: #1438969

Change-Id: I4a82e2435d176f3d9336d7f0dab9726c063840b9
Co-authored-by: Armando Migliaccio <armamig@gmail.com>

commit_message:
Don't unregister if we didn't register

There are ways to build RHEL images with local yum repos that don't
require registration, so there are cases where we don't want to
unregister at the end of the build.  While this can be done
manually today with REG_HALT_UNREGISTER, it's better to make the
unregister script smarter so it won't try to unregister an image
that wasn't registered in the first place.

Change-Id: I4a710953d72c2ca374159e6cc3b201b354b89b2b
Closes-Bug: 1434431

commit_message:
Add Ceilometer support to DevStack plugin

This simply enables Designate to emit the necessary notifications, as a
first step towards Ceilometer integration.

Change-Id: I5183df447d80cdfbd39f6fc178c05a3f5d09dd4b

commit_message:
DevStack: Akamai/Dyn Support for Jenkins Credentials and Exercises

The Jenkins credential binding plugin will provide the secrets in
a single colon separated environment variable, so we pass this
through and update the Akamai and Dyn drivers to support reading
from it.

The exercices are also now fixed, where both the Akami and Dyn
backends would result in more than 1 NS records, the original
counters were off.

Change-Id: I7bb37e9671dae34b47abf9bf092d90e8ba248ccb

commit_message:
Allows Javelin to specify Swift role

Javelin assumes that the role needed by Swift is 'Member'. This patch
allows the possibility to specify something else, while keeping the
default value to 'Member' if nothing is specified.

Change-Id: I672f3efa8c00d55cc9bb644783e40a11e548018c

commit_message:
Tweak authenticate event definition

The event definition for an authenticate event is simply:
  identity.authenticate

there is no trailing period.

Change-Id: Ie9c3fd66abea2b02411e6f3a01051f59a94bf284
Closes-Bug: 1439538

commit_message:
cluster: install pcs package on Debian/Ubuntu

The python-pcs package is the packet construction set [1]. This package
has been shipped with Debian/Ubuntu for quite a long time.
For some reason the pacemaker/corosync configuration system [2] has been
packaged for Ubuntu under the name `python-pcs'. Use the correct name
(that is, `pcs', like its RPM counterpart) to resolve the collision.

[1] https://github.com/gvnn3/PCS
[2] https://github.com/feist/pcs

Note: this patch should be merged along with the following ones:
https://review.fuel-infra.org/4522
https://review.openstack.org/164111

blueprint support-ubuntu-trusty

Change-Id: I460b550869d0fe0c4742c198ebc8c54b9548eae8
Signed-off-by: Sergii Golovatiuk <sgolovatiuk@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
glance-manage db load_metadefs does not load all resource_type_associations

The glance-manage db load_metadefs should create
metadef_namespace_resource_types entries for all resource_type_associations
listed in a given .json file. Unfortunately, load_metadefs currently,
only creates a metadef_namespace_resource_types entry if the associated
resource_type is new.

There are 6 resource_types and as a result only 6
metadef_namespace_resource_types records are generated instead of the
expected 31 (as of this writing).

The fix will now generate all metadef_namespace_resource_types.

Change-Id: I645f05620c134eac816cd9baf739b4305b307667
Closes-Bug: 1434761

commit_message:
Fix issue with non-determenistic ordering in networkx sorting

In current master of networkx it is possible to specify fabric
that will be used for internal graph data structures.

To avoid non determinitic issues with ordering we need to use
OrderedDict that will return same order of keys even with different
hash seeds. OrderedDict should be used for storing order of
nodes inserted in graph, and for dependencies between nodes
in graph.

Changed tests to verify that order will be same with different
hash seeds.

Networkx 1.9.1 (one which we are using)

  http://bit.ly/1CcgdBs

Networkx change with fixed code

  http://bit.ly/1al6Tpq

Change-Id: I16a880fe996a03645c0f79e3156ae403b9f006f5
Closes-Bug: 1438203

rest: do not use expect_error in tests

Using that with status= confuse webtest as it does not check the status
code at all.

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-03-31 15:15:58.000000000', 'message': "rest: enhance metric retrieval in controllers

This fetch the metric information earlier in the API, so it avoids doing
more than one request on the indexer to retrieve a metric info. The
upside is that we detect also non existent metric earlier.

The downside is that we have to fetch the details of a metric (i.e. the
archive policy detail) on each call because most controllers except to
have this details near them. That shouldn't be a large issue, it ends up
simplifying the API a bit since you don't have to explicitely request
the details of a metric anymore.

Change-Id: If0af07fdb83b05e6172141ebc4687cf4de7e51c9
"}, {'created': '2015-03-31 18:01:13.000000000', 'message': "rest: enhance metric retrieval in controllers

commit_message:
rest: enhance metric retrieval in controllers

This fetch the metric information earlier in the API, so it avoids doing
more than one request on the indexer to retrieve a metric info. The
upside is that we detect also non existent metric earlier.

The downside is that we have to fetch the details of a metric (i.e. the
archive policy detail) on each call because most controllers except to
have this details near them. That shouldn't be a large issue, it ends up
simplifying the API a bit since you don't have to explicitely request
the details of a metric anymore.

Change-Id: If0af07fdb83b05e6172141ebc4687cf4de7e51c9

commit_message:
Cleans default declaration nullable=False from heat objects

In Heat objects, the default value of nullable attribute is
set in many of the object's fields, which is not required
as oslo object Field defines nullable as False by default

Change-Id: I0164b64c043816f624aeba19561a4a5f8d36689d
Closes-bug: #1439957

commit_message:
Revert "Consider whether node has public network for network-verify config"

Reason:
http://jenkins-product.srt.mirantis.net:8080/job/6.1.ubuntu.smoke_neutron/206/console

Net-checker tries to test public vlan even with one controller 
but it cannot receive any packets in this case as it sends packets
between nodes only, not within one node.

Test with revert:
http://jenkins-product.srt.mirantis.net:8080/view/custom_iso/job/6.1.custom_system_test/14/

This reverts commit 424ae2fa4ae299887fe04f0c61449e92ebd2178e.

Change-Id: I713d650256fbfe84186c66691442d12cf47f1b56

commit_message:
[Vm] Restore fixed IP support in boot_runcommand_delete

Changes:
    * restore argument `use_floating_ip' for scenario
      VMTasks.boot_runcommand_delete, which controls whether to use
      floating or fixed IP for SSH connection
    * fix for exceptions.ScriptError

Change-Id: I92820954079a62a7e619d136527f13008e5768f9
Closes-Bug: #1427313

commit_message:
Zero downtime config reload (glance-control)

Update glance-control to send a SIGHUP rather than
perform a start/stop for the 'reload' operation.

This allows picking up new configuration values without
interrupting the service.

Closes-bug: 1436275
Change-Id: I5a653daa3e582b665c0a2c402cf2d7c9e47e1c38

commit_message:
Make almost all the element scripts as e/u/pipefail

Following the latest dib-lint reporting, make sure almost all the
scripts are enabling -e, -u, and pipefail.  This eases the discovery of
failing commands, and the usage of unset variables.

There are few exceptions with flags not set:

* elements/hadoop-hdp/install.d/40-install-hdp, set -e
  when installing HDP 2.0, it tries to install tez, which does not seem
  to exist in Hortonworks' repositories

* elements/ssh/install.d/33-ssh, set -e
  the version of augtool (part of augeas 0.10) in older Ubuntu versions
  (like Precise, needed by the cloudera plugin) exits with wrong return
  values in autosave mode

* elements/storm/install.d/60-storm, set -e
  It tries to change the permission of /etc/supervisord.conf, which does
  not seem to exist

Change-Id: Ic1314639dfc6a66c48ca87b6820707a2b0cb1dbd
Partial-Bug: #1435306

[{'created': '2015-04-07 10:33:32.000000000', 'message': 'Do not use $TARGET_ROOT in install.d scripts

$TARGET_ROOT is only usable in root.d, block-device.d, and cleanup.d
scripts, as other types are executed within the chroot already.

Change-Id: I92b5728ca65072140cce2f0b531b9a293001e03c
'}]
commit_message:
Do not use $TARGET_ROOT in install.d scripts

$TARGET_ROOT is only usable in root.d, block-device.d, and cleanup.d
scripts, as other types are executed within the chroot already.

Change-Id: I92b5728ca65072140cce2f0b531b9a293001e03c

commit_message:
Fix support for PostgreSQL

https://review.openstack.org/152337 - This is a reference for dropping support
for downgrade() in migrations that add values to enums since it's hard to
delete values from a enum type in postgres.

Change-Id: I61e86935b508986470447f02fa2f4b6c9d9f8afd

commit_message:
Fixing python 3 imcompatiblity in common.utils

Also, renaming some values to "coding" and "quality" to get
a little closer to the RFC names of "coding" and "qvalue".
This is still ugly though. We'll have to come back through
here and clean this up some more at a later date.

Change-Id: I050e60cbf483f5d6f323dfa06393cbcbb2fc2852

commit_message:
image/centos: umount filesystems under the image build directory

... before trying to remove that directory. No busy loopback devices
are hanging around after a failed build any more.

Closes-Bug: #1427170

Change-Id: I72a6e58f0501e73996964bc033556747b56c43bf

commit_message:
mysql: use install-packages and pkg-map elements

Make use of the install-packages element, so it is easier to specify the
packages using a declarative yaml file.
To keep the different list of packages depending on the distro, make use
of the pkg-map element so the right packages per-family and per-distro
(Fedora, in this case) can be chosen.

Change-Id: I64797fd075204609d54dbd01c896acb7ab638a29

commit_message:
Start caching large-sized resources

Use the cache-url script (in the element cache-url) to download and
cache resources which might be expensive (mostly because of their size)
to fetch every time.
As the shared cache ($DIB_IMAGE_CACHE) is available only when running
the root.d elements, move the download phases to root.d scripts.

Change-Id: Iec3e0f92e62c4c9542487a3c228ba8f9e884e5dd

commit_message:
Catalog Index Service

Implements: blueprint catalog-index-service

* Glance Index and Search API Implementation
* Tool for indexing metadefinition resources and images from Glance
database into Elasticsearch index

This is awesome!!

One inline comment, I think it's just a typo."}, {'account_id': 6525, 'date': '2015-04-03 02:19:37.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 4.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-04-03 02:25:26.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Verified+1

- gate-puppet-openstacklib-puppet-unit-3.4 http://logs.openstack.org/02/170002/4/check/gate-puppet-openstacklib-puppet-unit-3.4/79e3f82/ : SUCCESS in 1m 07s
- gate-puppet-openstacklib-puppet-unit-3.6 http://logs.openstack.org/02/170002/4/check/gate-puppet-openstacklib-puppet-unit-3.6/656eae0/ : SUCCESS in 1m 10s
- gate-puppet-openstacklib-puppet-unit-3.7 http://logs.openstack.org/02/170002/4/check/gate-puppet-openstacklib-puppet-unit-3.7/e55cac6/ : SUCCESS in 1m 09s
- gate-puppet-openstacklib-puppet-beaker-rspec http://logs.openstack.org/02/170002/4/check/gate-puppet-openstacklib-puppet-beaker-rspec/0d0ad6a/ : FAILURE in 38s (non-voting)
- gate-puppet-openstacklib-puppet-syntax-future http://logs.openstack.org/02/170002/4/check/gate-puppet-openstacklib-puppet-syntax-future/eac3164/ : SUCCESS in 50s (non-voting)'}, {'account_id': 6525, 'date': '2015-04-03 02:41:57.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

> Is there a way we could make the transition a little smoother by still allowing auth_url when using v2.0?

Ok just to make sure there isn't any confusion, my understanding is that auth_url (--os-auth-url) is when using authentication requests where url (--os-url) is for using the service directly (via a token). This is independently of the API version.

That said OSC is using it's own convention/configuration defaults (got that from a keystone developer) which adds an extra interface layer. 

This is why I'm tempted to minimize the interface (openstack provider) to the interface (OSC) which interfaces with keystone (API). For instance I would leave the parameters as loose as possible, whether RC, ENV or OSC params are used and just pass whatever is provided. Openstacklib to submit and check if authentication is successful or not, if not, then not enough credentials where provided. This way we offer more flexibility.

Fixed the copy/paste type. Thank you"}, {'account_id': 8482, 'date': '2015-04-03 05:34:49.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

> my understanding is that auth_url (--os-auth-url) is when using authentication requests where url (--os-url) is for using the service directly (via a token). This is independently of the API version.

I think you're right, my mistake. I had thought I'd seen --os-auth-url work with the token in some cases. Still, the keystone module is using auth_url in combination with the token (http://git.openstack.org/cgit/stackforge/puppet-keystone/tree/lib/puppet/provider/keystone.rb#n28) so changing it to 'url' here breaks the keystone module. I'm inclined to try to avoid that by allowing both url and auth_url here. On the other hand, since the keystone module is in the middle of an overhaul anyway we could change both at the same time.

> That said OSC is using it's own convention/configuration defaults (got that from a keystone developer) which adds an extra interface layer.
> This is why I'm tempted to minimize the interface (openstack provider) to the interface (OSC) which interfaces with keystone (API).

I don't know how possible that is, but in the interest of getting as close to that as possible I think it makes more sense to use auth_url for both types of URL, ignoring the convention set by openstackclient."}, {'account_id': 11491, 'date': '2015-04-03 09:33:39.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review+1

Wow! Gilles is in the place ;-)'}, {'account_id': 8482, 'date': '2015-04-03 16:29:06.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

I'm going to -1 because I'd still like to see a plan to get this merged quickly without leaving keystone broken for any period of time."}, {'account_id': 9983, 'date': '2015-04-06 14:38:40.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

Does this mean we will break backwards compatibility?  That is, if there is a module that still wants to use v2 auth, it will not be able to?'}, {'account_id': 8482, 'date': '2015-04-06 16:41:51.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

> Does this mean we will break backwards compatibility? That is, if there is a module that still wants to use v2 auth, it will not be able to?

I don't think this breaks backwards compatibility, except for the url/auth_url bit. The following command works:

 openstack --os-username admin --os-password fyby-tet --os-project-name admin --os-auth-url http://127.0.0.1:35357/v2.0 project list"}, {'account_id': 6525, 'date': '2015-04-07 04:58:46.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

Yes the intent is to stay backward compatible as much as possible.

Also to have keystone module aligned, this patch is needed:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/171044/

This way we can have a clear path for auth_url and url'}, {'account_id': 8482, 'date': '2015-04-07 06:46:16.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4: Code-Review+2

Whoever +A's, please look at https://review.openstack.org/#/c/171044 first and merge both."}, {'account_id': 3153, 'date': '2015-04-07 15:53:20.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review+2 Workflow+1'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-04-07 15:53:28.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: -Verified

- gate-puppet-openstacklib-puppet-unit-3.6 http://logs.openstack.org/02/170002/4/gate/gate-puppet-openstacklib-puppet-unit-3.6/53c670e/ : SUCCESS in 1m 01s
- gate-puppet-openstacklib-puppet-unit-3.7 http://logs.openstack.org/02/170002/4/gate/gate-puppet-openstacklib-puppet-unit-3.7/14f40c0/ : SUCCESS in 1m 02s'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-04-07 16:00:49.000000000', 'content': 'Change has been successfully merged into the git repository.'}]
revisions:
[{'created': '2015-04-02 05:46:36.000000000', 'message': "Targeting Keystone V3 API support

  The default domain (id 'default', name 'Default') is where the V2
tenants/users are defined. So V3, which is now the default API's version
can and should be used.  Beeing able to use V3 domains needs to be
supported by specifying the domain name for a project/user.

This patch :
- Adds project and user domain names
- Renames tenant (v2) as project (v3)
- Renames os-auth-url to os-url, when using an authicated token against a
  service url, to distinct them from each other, as in OSC
(opentackclient)
- Updates newparam(:auth) accordingly to describe v2/v3 credential
  examples

Note: Keystone API v2 is deprecated [1]

[1] http://docs.openstack.org/developer/keystone/http-api.html#should-i-use-v2-0-or-v3

Change-Id: I72f79129a6875eb433eeb8a62f928e7210db134a

(opentackclient)

  examples

Note: Keystone API v2 is deprecated [1]

[1] http://docs.openstack.org/developer/keystone/http-api.html#should-i-use-v2-0-or-v3

commit_message:
Targeting Keystone V3 API support

  The default domain (id 'default', name 'Default') is where the V2
tenants/users are defined. So V3, which is now the default API's version
can and should be used.  Beeing able to use V3 domains needs to be
supported by specifying the domain name for a project/user.

This patch :
- Adds project and user domain names
- Renames tenant (v2) as project (v3)
- Renames os-auth-url to os-url, when using an authicated token against a
  service url, to distinct them from each other, as in OSC
(opentackclient)
- Updates newparam(:auth) accordingly to describe v2/v3 credential
  examples

Note: Keystone API v2 is deprecated [1]

[1] http://docs.openstack.org/developer/keystone/http-api.html#should-i-use-v2-0-or-v3

Change-Id: I72f79129a6875eb433eeb8a62f928e7210db134a

commit_message:
Implementation of bandwidth-limitation blueprint

Limitation of upload and download http bandwidth.
Monkey patching of socket.recv and socket.sendall methods.
After every invocation of recv or sendall methods sleeps calculated amount of time.

Change-Id: I0a3478fe9f5fca4a0cb3fa0826447b05cf22d42d
Implements: blueprint bandwithd-limitation

commit_message:
Increase treshold for running processes for zabbix

Modern OS can run much more than 300 processes, so zabbix warn every
time about it. Increased value to 500.

Change-Id: Icbcfa2009e312a66c84f3de5f16b53c95052553b
Closes-Bug: #1434118

commit_message:
Adding a functional test that uses python-magnumclient

A new test that just uses the python magnum client modules
to make an actual REST call from the functional test harness.

Related-Bug: #1440125

commit_message:
Fix handling of filtering params

This switches all the v2 code to use the base classes method for parsing
filtering params from the query parameters.

Change-Id: Ibc620ca2ff8eb021a1fea1dbbb3ea21705027381
Closes-Bug: #1440840

I never really liked the v1 behaviour where you would provide a 'name or id' to the cli and it would have to figure out your intention.

What happens here, if, for example you create an image with a name which is also a valid image id?
Or someone creates a new a public image, or shares an image, which has the same name as your image?

It also affects the efficiency of the call, as multiple calls have to be made to ascertain if an image exists or not.

I'd prefer if cli input is unambiguous."}, {'account_id': 455, 'date': '2015-03-31 10:02:35.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

When we do an image-list using the v2 api more detail is returned by the server for each image than is displayed by the client, eg:

 {"images": [{"status": "queued", "name": "img1", "tags": [], "container_format": "bare", "created_at": "2015-03-05T13:22:07Z", "size": 0, "disk_format": "raw", "updated_at": "2015-03-05T13:22:07Z", "visibility": "private", "self": "/v2/images/74530abf-54a2-45f3-ac94-23c37e9e215d", "min_disk": 0, "protected": false, "id": "74530abf-54a2-45f3-ac94-23c37e9e215d", "file": "/v2/images/74530abf-54a2-45f3-ac94-23c37e9e215d/file", "checksum": null, "owner": "e30399c2175c4a4ba5d1d76dbea6d15d", "virtual_size": null, "min_ram": 0, "schema": "/v2/schemas/image"}], "schema": "/v2/schemas/images", "first": "/v2/images?limit=20"}

I wonder if we could do something like add a '--detail' flag, eg 'glance --os-image-api-version 2 image-list --detail' to show each image's details? Then we could do  'image-list --detail --name myname' to effectively 'show' all image(s) with a certain name.'}, {'account_id': 8127, 'date': '2015-03-31 11:04:15.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

As far as I remember, removing "get by name or id" logic in v2 was intentional, as names are not unique and are even not required at all (also, as Stuart has mentioned above, name and id conflict is indeed possible). So, I'd say that the bug 1369302 is Invalid.

Also, the proposed solution is incorrect: v2 client should not use apiclient.base.Resource classes, as the v2 objects are warlock-generated and should not be hardcoded at all.'}, {'account_id': 6159, 'date': '2015-03-31 11:33:58.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review-2

Hey Yatin,

Thanks a lot for the patch. As others have mentioned, this behavior is expected in the v2. The old "name or id" behavior is not desired because it brings in inconsistency in the API and it makes the user experience painful.

I'm blocking this patch to make sure we're all on the same page. It'd be better if you could abandon it yourself. If you think there's a better case for this behavior, feel free to bring it up'}, {'account_id': 13861, 'date': '2015-03-31 11:37:45.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

Hi Stuart,
I agree that multiple checks(as i can see calls to api are only made for only one case i.e either name or id) are required in this case(to find whether image id or image name is provided), but  for an end user, we should definitely provide this feature so that one can view image by both name and id.
Also, in the case you specified(creation of image with a name as same as existing image-id) this will fail, as it checks for image-id first, and it will show the details of image with the existing image-id. But i am not getting a case where user will create an image with name as similar to uuid. As a user i think, image name should be such that images are easily identifiable.'}, {'account_id': 13861, 'date': '2015-03-31 11:48:22.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

Hi Alexender,
Can you please share the intention for removing "get by name or id" logic. I just want to know the discussions done under this. I agree names are not required for creating images, but as a user one can create images by name as he wishes, and then if he wishes to see details of image by name then what should he do. As you mentioned, v2 client should not use apiclient.base.Resource classes, i am not aware of this, can you tell the workaround for this.

Thanks'}, {'account_id': 13861, 'date': '2015-03-31 11:53:08.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

Hi Flavio,
I will abandon the change as asked by you, once all my queries are cleared, This would help me in finding some better solution. Just to know, in what cases: this makes the user experience painful.

Thanks'}, {'account_id': 13861, 'date': '2015-04-05 14:20:19.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

@Stuart, @Alexender, @Flavio any update on this, please answer my query, so that i can abandon this change.'}, {'account_id': 6159, 'date': '2015-04-07 12:00:49.000000000', 'content': "Abandoned

@yatin I believe the main reason behind this was consistency. Accepting names for accessing images was confusing and users didn't know whether using names/ids was the right thing to do. In addition to this, they also started mixing names/ids for image members, etc.

To avoid these kind of confusions, it's better to just use the one field we guarantee to be unique, the id."}, {'account_id': 13861, 'date': '2015-04-07 15:14:28.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

Thanks, @flavio for your response'}]

commit_message:
glance image-show v2 now works with image name also

glance image-show v2 now works with both image name and image id.
This help users to see image details by using image name

Change-Id: Iee784d881d39b9dfd920ab14267e5fecf158f1ac
Closes-Bug: #1369302

commit_message:
indexer: return resource objects rather than dict

We used to return dict from the indexer, and then convert them to
object, and then sometimes encoding them as JSON.

We know makes the indexer returns directly object that have the right
interface to be directly encoded as JSON. That reduces the number of
object we have to create down the path and improves performance.

This is done for all methods that handles resources.

Change-Id: I0e6034083f1fd8f55d924dd0eaaee17ffb35c691

commit_message:
Expose Rest Api access to mtu attributes

Exposing Read only access to mtu attributes via the network
api calls so GET operations can be performed. Tied in the
mtu attribute with create network call and use the config
default. Also included unit tests to cover default and
override config case for segment_mtu attribute.

Partially Implements: blueprint mtu-selection-and-advertisement

Change-Id: I811c288bdd96691a96d1721eb29354c0911edf3a

commit_message:
Disable test on non-supported environment

Disable non-supported environment py33 py34 py26 pypy

Since CI folks recommended dropping py33 for all jobs and they all
would get cleaned up, so the new target will be py34 and we should
enable py34 as soon as it has been supported in magnum.

Change-Id: I692f9c7f925e0c5c9744313257125a1d499cbe70
Closes-Bug: #1412230

commit_message:
Remove building of pam+noaudit and place in copr instead

COPR is a repository for third party packages built by the Fedora build
system.  Instead of dragging in 250MB of dependencies to build pam, build
externally and load only the RPM into the image.

The pam that is built externally is built with the --with-noaudit flag
and a Provides: pam line.

Change-Id: I28396996943d2fdc12b253faf62af8623c8b0e73

commit_message:
Consider whether node has public network for network-verify config

Public VLANs should be added into network-verify configuration only
for nodes which have br-ex to be configured.

Closes-Bug: #1397369
Change-Id: If3ec552b895e5e4f9763c18e23f3a3b7461e20c7

commit_message:
libvirtd provides was removed from centos7.1

the libvirtd package "Provides" wwas removed from the libvirt packaging.
To workaround this problem just install libvirt-daemon in CentOS 7.1 or Fedora
20+.

WIthout this change, an install of libvirtd does not actually install
libvirtd.  The yum tool will not fail if libvirtd is specified so we weren't
catching this in the build.

Change-Id: I81e64f6f659aa0466369dad4b0574ebb24c99555

commit_message:
Changes to plugin.sh

1) Install networking-ovn with devstack common functions 
   (inplace install)

2) Add remote for local manager (used by OVSDB IDL)

3) Remove openvswitch-common package as well because 
   of dependency with openvswitch-switch

Change-Id: Ib0908a13dafa741d015b3ff046a4b79b2125451c

commit_message:
Fix typo in ini block section

Without the block directive, the generated HTML
has both the ini css class as well as the python css class.

<div class="code ini highlight-python">

instead of

<div class="highlight-ini">

Related-Bug: #1439920

Change-Id: I981eef92cdfbc6f125731096b939cefc8ad2d15e

commit_message:
Add Neutron subnet-create with subnetpool

Add neutron subnet-create with subnetpool feature.
With subnetpool, user can either have prefixlen or cidr.
The cidr for subnet is optional parameter with subnetpool.

Change-Id: I795b233985f9ab7cb59d7318a5d7a1e9c4431a1c

If we want to revert the renaming, I think we need to change the setup.cfg as well. Otherwise the meter would never be able to published out by the pipeline.

b.t.w. Ildiko, Edwin is looking at ways to tweak in the api layer to see if we can keep the end user un-impacted while still having that kind of new name in database. Don't know if he could make it by RC1 though, just an information."}, {'account_id': 9562, 'date': '2015-04-03 08:16:36.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 4491, 'date': '2015-04-03 08:16:47.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

in the meanwhile, let's see if edwin could come up with his patch in time :)"}, {'account_id': 9562, 'date': '2015-04-03 08:24:57.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

Hi Lianhao,

Thanks for the heads up, I messed up with grep it seems, fixed in the next patch set.

As for fixing the issue, please note that not only the API layer is affected. We use the mete name in the pipeline.yaml.

As for the API layer it seemed tricky to me, as if you request for a meter with name 'XY', then you need the result with the name 'XY'. Which is fine for the samples stored with the original meter name, but will be a bigger translation issue for the ones with the new name.

So for me it seems a bigger task and I don't want to risk a half solution because of the RC1 rush. We can add the new name in Liberty and keep the old deprecated in that cycle, so we will have time to fix this properly.

Best Regards,
Ildiko"}, {'account_id': 2813, 'date': '2015-04-03 08:28:32.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+2 Workflow+1'}, {'account_id': 9562, 'date': '2015-04-03 08:43:41.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

@Lianhao: sure, also many thanks to Edwin. :) I will wait with touching the docs in OS Manuals too.

commit_message:
Use old name of 'hardware.ipmi.node.temperature'

Use old name of the 'hardware.ipmi.node.temperature' as currently there
is no proper deprecation process for meters.

DocImpact

Partially Closes-Bug: #1439766

Change-Id: Ic71bcda4008f1b4090e0d9c8908201440abb02a4

[{'created': '2015-04-03 11:51:05.000000000', 'message': "Remove 'samples:groupby' from the Capabilities list

The 'samples:groupby' field in capabilities does not mark a real
functionality, but can cause confusion, therefore it is removed
from that list. The example in the documentation was also updated.

commit_message:
Remove 'samples:groupby' from the Capabilities list

The 'samples:groupby' field in capabilities does not mark a real
functionality, but can cause confusion, therefore it is removed
from that list. The example in the documentation was also updated.

Change-Id: Id902c3c7d55b5ca11bbc8b909b0b07f487887fc1
closes-Bug: #1440031

commit_message:
Skip SSL tests because some platforms do not enable SSLv3

For "damned good security reasons" (POODLE) some platforms have
patched out SSLv3 from OpenSSL. Because Evenetlet cannot be configured
for specific versions (or ciphers) and httplib is extremely limited,
the tests for SSL have been explicitly skipped. These tests should
be potentially re-enabled in the functional suite for SSL terminated
endpoints.

This comes back to "do not terminate SSL in the eventlet wsgi" that
was determined in bug 1381365.

Change-Id: Ic4b446ceee9034de5b6530c2d79d798a903fcbbf
Related-Bug: #1381365
Closes-Bug: #1435174

commit_message:
Add missing mock for test_create_cleaning_ports_fail

The test:
ironic.tests.dhcp.test_neutron.TestNeutron.test_create_cleaning_ports_fail
was taking over two seconds to complete. On failure, it was issuing
a call to _rollback_cleaning_ports, which calls Neutron, that was
not mocked.

Change-Id: I2846061915015960c87f86931c4329ecaf9dbf1e

commit_message:
Add a file handler for shotgun's logger

  Add LOG_FILE variable to shotgun.settings.
  Add FileHandler in logging.py module.

Closes-Bug: 1318516

commit_message:
params: update libvirt

In RHEL7 & CentOS7 and Fedora*, libvirt package is libvirt-daemon-kvm

* https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Getting_started_with_virtualization#Installing_the_virtualization_packages

Change-Id: If27d09767c159a795462a47c6897a572f284a39f

I still need to do further testing -- I think you mean that whatever project is in conf.py is the project that Launchpad link will prefill?'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-03-10 15:18:18.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Verified+1

Of course we shouldn't have comments of the type "bug fix underway" in shipped code, so your comment changes do make sense. Thanks.

The real work that remains to be done is including relevant information in the bug link, such as source file, html file, version or whatever else is important. Doesn't have to be exactly the same as it's done currently I guess.
"I think you mean that whatever project is in conf.py is the project that Launchpad link will prefill?" Yes, that's what I meant, though it's merely an illustration of what I have in mind.

Generally, I believe that the "relevant information" I allude to above must be put into conf.py so that Sphinx can pick it up and put it into the log-a-bug link. I don't know, however, how conf.py will be crafted and where above information is coming from, since I don't know the environment all this will live in.'}, {'account_id': 964, 'date': '2015-03-11 20:36:41.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

So, my understanding is that the conf.py should be shipped with every doc "project" that will use this theme. For example, in openstack-manuals repo, we are busily converting the xml files in the doc/user-guide and doc/user-guide-admin directories into RST in a playground-user-guide/source file. The playground-user-guide has its own conf.py. I'll do some testing with that content, which is really where this theme will be used, to see if we can put all the info in conf.py. Thank you for all the great comments, commit messages, questions, and answers! Really outstanding work here.'}, {'account_id': 964, 'date': '2015-03-11 20:37:31.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Meant to add a link. here's the conf.py for the testbed migration user guide:

https://github.com/openstack/openstack-manuals/blob/master/doc/playground-user-guide/source/conf.py"}, {'account_id': 6547, 'date': '2015-03-15 16:47:34.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

(4 comments)

git show (perhaps using git format) should give you the information about a change.

We use for each book a separate conf.py file, so can add variables specific to a book to it, e.g. the name of it.'}, {'account_id': 15002, 'date': '2015-03-16 07:50:17.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

(3 comments)

I'll apply a few updates but first need to recover from a disk crash on my PC. 

We still don't know how to get the RST source file name and the finale document's URL into conf.py; probably via the build process."}, {'account_id': 15002, 'date': '2015-03-18 11:25:23.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

Tried to get source file name and URL from Sphinx/Jinja, but it doesn't quite work. It should however be possible to tweak this by adding relevant path components.

This is what I tried (essentially copied from Sphinx' built-in basic theme): 

        {%- if show_source and has_source and sourcename %}
            var sourceFile = "Source: {{ pathto(sourcename,1) }}"
            var docUrl = "URL: {{ pathto(sourcename) }}"
        {%- endif %}

On the other hand, I am able to retrieve the SHA from git and pass it into the html template thanks to a handful of lines in conf.py.'}, {'account_id': 15002, 'date': '2015-03-19 05:57:16.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 4.'}, {'account_id': 15002, 'date': '2015-03-19 05:58:44.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

Hi Bernd, I've been playing around with Elasticsearch during my week off, and in doing so have had Sphinx build json with the jsonbuilder. In that json there's a filename field extracted, but oddly it was with a .txt extension instead of .rst. These are also output to a _source directory, I suppose so that if you use the html_show_source_link configuration in your templates http://sphinx-doc.org/config.html#confval-html_show_sourcelink. So Sphinx has the filename somewhere, I wonder if we'll have to output json also to get this kind of metadata we need for this feature. Just thinking aloud here."}, {'account_id': 15002, 'date': '2015-03-19 13:54:43.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

Hmmm, I wonder whether the filename and the _sources/filename you see in the Json output is the {{ sourcename }} variable and {{ pathto(sourcename,1) }} which I use in the current patchlevel. The result is not too useful:

Release: 1.0 on 2015-03-19 14:38
SHA: 61bca5ec2b0a7413a0b5ea00238f8c735aeeb45c
Source: index.txt
URL: index.txt.html

Note here as well the txt extension. 
"pathto()", it turns out, returns the path to the file relative to the build directory and relative to _sources directory, when using an additional option. 

But I will try jsonbuilder, perhaps it contains more info or inspires me how to solve this.'}, {'account_id': 964, 'date': '2015-03-31 16:03:32.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

(1 comment)

So, the real reason we want to report the source file in the doc bug is so that people who report bugs might be encouraged to edit the file themselves. So ideally we could offer a link to git.openstack.org or github.com. More inline.'}, {'account_id': 964, 'date': '2015-04-02 14:57:43.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 5.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-04-02 15:04:03.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5: Verified+1

The current code can't work because there is Jinja2 code in the logabug() function in docs.js. It seems that Sphinx doesn't process docs.js with Jinja2, which leads to a Javascript syntax error.

Moving logabug() back to layout.html does away with this. I take the liberty to do that, since I also have a solution for the source file link - a simple call to "pwd" in conf.py and subsequent text processing to turn the absolute file path into a git.openstack.org link. 

Let me know whether this is satisfactory on a functionality level. I will look into the Jinja2 issue, as I understand it's not good form to put Javascript into HTML files.'}, {'account_id': 15002, 'date': '2015-04-06 03:29:34.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 7.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-04-06 03:29:58.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 7: Verified-1

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-03-01 04:35:13.000000000', 'message': '"log a bug" link added to Sphinx-based documentation

Current documentation is Docbook-based. Each page features two
"log a bug" links near the top and the bottom. This bug fix
modifies the openstackdocstheme in an attempt to do something
similar for future Sphinx-based documentation pages.

This is a partial fix, or perhaps not more than a proof of
concept. Some functionality is missing (see below); in addition,
I am not certain in which file and which form to put the
Javascript snippet that performs the magic.

Regarding coding style:
-----------------------
Currently, the code is at the end of layout.html and consists of
a JS script that modifies the href of the two <a> elements that
contain the launchpad links.
To achieve this, I also added IDs to these two elements,
"buglinktop" and "buglinkbottom" respectively, so that they can be
referenced in the JS code.

A better location for the code may be one of the *.js files under
..../static/js, perhaps docs.js as suggested by the bug submitter.

Regarding functionality:
------------------------
In the current DocBook-based implementation, a click on
"log a bug" opens a launchpad page with the bug summary and
further information prepopulated. Summary is the name of the
book, such as "Install Guide for Ubuntu - Icehouse"; an example for
Further Information is:

    -----------------------------------
    Built: 2015-01-06T17:15:01 00:00
    git SHA: 233c8098bbdc5bc83bbd74403650feb6610f4b95
    URL:
    http://docs.openstack.org/icehouse/install-guide/install/apt/content/
    source File:
    file:/home/jenkins/workspace/openstack-manuals-tox-doc-publishdocs/doc/install-guide/bk_openstackinstallguide.xml
    xml:id: openstack-install-manual-icehouse

I don't know where to look for most of this data, including the book
title. The solution might be  putting information into conf.py; right
now, for example, the JS snippet uses the "project", "release", "version"
and "html_last_updated_fmt" variables from conf.py.

Thus, I am submitting this partial fix but need conversations with
people more knowledgeable about the Sphinx environment to complete it.

Change-Id: Ib60146d993ff67fc3f8fd8703cdad1935f7ec6bb
Partial-Bug: #1421799
